The Golden Age of Radio: Program 49 - April, 1974 - Edgar Bergen
Old Time Radio Program Logs By Frank Passage and Others

infos.info: The show was on NBC and then later on CBS. - There were 30, 60 and 55 minute versions. - The show had a featured sketch, ' The Bickersons' - ----------------------------------------------------------------------- - Catch-phrases from the show: - Charlie. ' I'll clip ya! So help me, I'll mow ya down!' - Edgar. ' Mortimer, how can you be so stupid?' - Ersel Twing. ' Friends, and you are my friends. Friends....' - ' Charlie,' - ' Mortimer' - ' Effie' - Charlie and Mortimer were regular guests to the program, while Effie was more sporadic.  - Coca-Cola took over sponsorship late in the program's run, though no year is given here. - Source: Buxton and Owen, ' The Big Broadcast

people.character: wrote the Adam and Eve skit
